During a press briefing, Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin and National Security Adviser General H.R. McMaster discussed the new financial sanctions on the Venezuelan dictatorship imposed by President Trump. The sanctions are aimed at targeting the means with which the Maduro regime can accumulate debt and enrich its corrupt officials. The United States will continue to support the Venezuelan people until their rights and democracy are fully restored. Homeland Security Adviser Tom Bossert also provided an update on preparations for Hurricane Harvey. The administration is closely monitoring the situation and ensuring that the American people are fully briefed on the storm. Finally, Press Secretary Sarah Sanders addressed questions regarding Treasury Secretary Mnuchin's recent remarks on tax reform and the President's response to the violence in Charlottesville.